```
sdbusplus::message::object_path objectPath(pcieDevicePath);
std::string& devName =  objectPath.filename();
```

The statement would need to be like
```
         if(ec)
         {
                if (ec.value() != EBADR)
                {
                    BMCWEB_LOG_ERROR
                        << "DBUS response error for getAssociationEndPoints: "
                        << ec.value();
                    messages::internalError(asyncResp->res);
                }
                return;  //<== Add
         }
```

Perhaps, then, wouldn't be good enough by setting after `getEmptyPCIeSlots()`?

```
        getEmptyPCIeSlots(asyncResp, pcieDevicePaths, name);
 >>      asyncResp->res.jsonValue[name + "@odata.count"] = pcieDeviceList.size();
```

Since `std::ranges` is used (and preferred) in bmcweb, this can be written as
```
    return std::ranges::find(pcieDevicePaths, pcieDevicePath) != 
                             pcieDevicePaths.end();
```

This part of logic & its children is to find the empty-slot by doing

```
getSubTreePaths() --> pcieDevicePaths
getSubTreePaths() -> pcieSlotPaths

for each  pcieSlotPaths
{
   getAssociationEndPoints() -> to check whether there is a pcieDevice
}
```

The logic seems simplified if we start with pcieSlots & check whether there is a pcieDevice using getAssociatedSubTreePaths()

```
getSubTreePaths() -> pcieSlotPaths
for each slot : pcieSlotPaths
{ 
   slotAssocPath = slot + "/contained_by";
   getAssociatedSubTreePaths(slotAssocPath, Item.PCIeDevice interface)
   if(empty ) {
       pcieSlot is empty
   }
}
```

This approach would reduce the first call `getSubTreePaths() --> pcieDevicePaths`, and I think the code would be clearer to read.

I don't think there are much of the performance differences.
Current code: (3 depths getSubTree or getAssoc Calls)

```
getPCIeDeviceList()
   dbus::utility::getSubTreePaths(...[](){
      getEmptyPCIeSlots() {
          dbus::utility::getSubTreePaths(...[](){
             handleGetEmptyPCIeSlots() {
               dbus::utility::getAssociationEndPoints();
             }
         });
   });
```

The new code: (2 depths getSubtree or getAssociatedSubTree)

```
getPCIeDeviceList()
   dbus::utility::getSubTreePaths(...[](){
         slotAssocPath = slot + "/contained_by";
        getAssociatedSubTreePaths( ..[](){
             if(ec || empty())
             {
             }
       });
```

It would be much more readable.
